<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870618-0104 </DOCNO><HL> EVI Group Buys a StakeIn Galveston-Houston Co.</HL><DD> 06/18/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> GHXTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><DATELINE> WASHINGTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   A group including EVI Inc., a Houston company engaged in making acquisitions of energy companies, said it bought a 9.35% stake in Galveston-Houston Co.'s common shares outstanding.    In a filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission, the group said it holds one million Galveston-Houston shares, all purchased on May 22 for a total of $1,550,000.    In New York Stock Exchange composite trading yesterday, Galveston-Houston closed at $3.50, unchanged.    The group said in the filing that it bought the shares in the Houston-based oilfield equipment and services company as an investment.    Officials of Galveston-Houston weren't available for comment. </TEXT></DOC>